    <title>Available plot marks</title>
    <para> Plot marks can be added to almost all linear (cartesian) graph types. They are used to
        emphasise the actual data points in the graph. The plot mark property is available as the
        instance variable "<code>$mark</code>" for the plot types that support plot marks. </para>
    <sect1>
        <title>Built in basic plot marks</title>
        <para>To embellishment a line plot with one of the built-in basic plot marks, say a a red
            diamond mark,  at each data point the following line has to be added to the graph
            script</para>
        <para>
            <programlisting>&lt;?php
$lineplot->mark->SetType(MARK_DIAMOND);
$lineplot->mark->SetFillColor('red');
?></programlisting>
        </para>
